AC   Q96T23; Q86X86; Q9H3L8; Q9NVZ8; Q9NYU0;
Remodeling and spacing factor 1 (Rsf-1) (Hepatitis B virus X-
associated protein) (HBV pX-associated protein 8) (p325 subunit of RSF
chromatin remodelling complex).
"HBXAP, a novel PHD-finger protein, possesses transcription repression
activity.";
"Hepatitis B virus pX interacts with HBXAP, a PHD finger protein to
coactivate transcription.";
"The status, quality, and expansion of the NIH full-length cDNA
project: the Mammalian Gene Collection (MGC).";
"Complete sequencing and characterization of 21,243 full-length human
cDNAs.";
"Functional analysis of the subunits of the chromatin assembly factor
RSF.";
"A probability-based approach for high-throughput protein
phosphorylation analysis and site localization.";
-!- FUNCTION: Required for assembly of regular nucleosome arrays by
    the RSF chromatin remodelling complex. Facilitates transcription
    of hepatitis B virus (HBV) genes by the pX transcription
    activator. In case of infection by HBV, together with pX, it
    represses TNF-alpha induced NF-kappaB transcription activation.
    Represses transcription when artificially recruited to chromatin
    by fusion to a heterogeneous DNA binding domain.
-!- SUBUNIT: Interacts with SMARCA5/SNF2H to form the RSF complex.
    Also binds the HBV pX/HBx protein, which is required to activate
    transcription of the viral genome.
-!- INTERACTION:
    O60264:SMARCA5; NbExp=3; IntAct=EBI-926768, EBI-352588;
    O60264:SMARCA5; NbExp=1; IntAct=EBI-926793, EBI-352588;
-!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Nucleus.
-!- ALTERNATIVE PRODUCTS:
